<emphasis id="EED9EAE9FFE7FF8880AB5FB11FD5FF57" bold="true" box="[151,438,186,212]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">Xenovarta viraktamathi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="F5EA5792FFE7FF8881805FB11C70FF57" box="[444,531,186,212]" pageId="2" pageNumber="446" rank="species">sp.nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation id="44962A7EFFE7FF88821E5FB11CC1FF57" box="[546,674,186,212]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1850,1872]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,298,1803]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,298,1829]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Xenovarta viraktamathi sp. nov. male 1, 2. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 3. Head and Pronotum; 4. Face; 5. Genital capsule, lateral view; 6. Pygofer lateral view; 7, 8. Aedeagus lateral and dorsal view; 9, 10. Valve and subgenital plates, dorsal and lateral view; 11.Style; 12. Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2615527/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">Figs. 1–12</figureCitation>
)
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DC1236FBFFE7FF8880AB5FD61D4FFEDF" blockId="2.[151,1436,152,1215]" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">
Pale green with red stripes (
<figureCitation id="44962A7EFFE7FF8881FA5FD61C56FF77" box="[454,565,221,244]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1850,1872]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,298,1803]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,298,1829]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Xenovarta viraktamathi sp. nov. male 1, 2. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 3. Head and Pronotum; 4. Face; 5. Genital capsule, lateral view; 6. Pygofer lateral view; 7, 8. Aedeagus lateral and dorsal view; 9, 10. Valve and subgenital plates, dorsal and lateral view; 11.Style; 12. Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2615527/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">Figs. 1&amp;2</figureCitation>
). Vertex lateral margin with a red stripe terminating into two black dot in dorsal view and ventrally with single dot (
<figureCitation id="44962A7EFFE7FF8882295E0B1C34FE94" box="[533,599,256,279]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1850,1872]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,298,1803]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,298,1829]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Xenovarta viraktamathi sp. nov. male 1, 2. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 3. Head and Pronotum; 4. Face; 5. Genital capsule, lateral view; 6. Pygofer lateral view; 7, 8. Aedeagus lateral and dorsal view; 9, 10. Valve and subgenital plates, dorsal and lateral view; 11.Style; 12. Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2615527/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Face yellow, anteriorly with boomerang shaped black spot with red margins (
<figureCitation id="44962A7EFFE7FF8880A35E291E87FEBA" box="[159,228,290,313]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1850,1872]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,298,1803]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,298,1829]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Xenovarta viraktamathi sp. nov. male 1, 2. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 3. Head and Pronotum; 4. Face; 5. Genital capsule, lateral view; 6. Pygofer lateral view; 7, 8. Aedeagus lateral and dorsal view; 9, 10. Valve and subgenital plates, dorsal and lateral view; 11.Style; 12. Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2615527/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Pronotum anteriorly orange yellow, rest pale green with four red stripes. Scutellum pale with two obscure orange stripes. Front wing pale green with red stripes (
<figureCitation id="44962A7EFFE7FF8882E15E4E1D7CFEDF" box="[733,799,325,348]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1850,1872]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,298,1803]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,298,1829]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Xenovarta viraktamathi sp. nov. male 1, 2. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 3. Head and Pronotum; 4. Face; 5. Genital capsule, lateral view; 6. Pygofer lateral view; 7, 8. Aedeagus lateral and dorsal view; 9, 10. Valve and subgenital plates, dorsal and lateral view; 11.Style; 12. Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2615527/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="94B76570FFE7FF8880FB5E631BE9FCE7" pageId="2" pageNumber="446" type="description">
<paragraph id="DC1236FBFFE7FF8880FB5E631A9AFD8A" blockId="2.[151,1436,152,1215]" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">
Head including eyes 0.9x width of pronotum, in dorsal view triangularly produced in front; vertex length as long as width across eyes; ocelli near anterior margin of vertex, close to eye; face 1.6x as long as wide; anteclypeus apically exceeding facial margin, slightly wider apically than at base, 0.34 times as long as frontoclypeus (
<figureCitation id="44962A7EFFE7FF88848E5EA61A97FE47" box="[1202,1268,429,452]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1850,1872]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,298,1803]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,298,1829]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Xenovarta viraktamathi sp. nov. male 1, 2. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 3. Head and Pronotum; 4. Face; 5. Genital capsule, lateral view; 6. Pygofer lateral view; 7, 8. Aedeagus lateral and dorsal view; 9, 10. Valve and subgenital plates, dorsal and lateral view; 11.Style; 12. Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2615527/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); frontoclypeus parallel sided; clypellus; antennae situated nearly upper margin of eye in facial view (
<figureCitation id="44962A7EFFE7FF88841B5EDB1A0BFE64" box="[1063,1128,464,487]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1850,1872]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,298,1803]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,298,1829]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Xenovarta viraktamathi sp. nov. male 1, 2. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 3. Head and Pronotum; 4. Face; 5. Genital capsule, lateral view; 6. Pygofer lateral view; 7, 8. Aedeagus lateral and dorsal view; 9, 10. Valve and subgenital plates, dorsal and lateral view; 11.Style; 12. Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2615527/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="44962A7EFFE7FF8884C85EDB1B50FE64" box="[1268,1331,464,487]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1850,1872]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,298,1803]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,298,1829]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Xenovarta viraktamathi sp. nov. male 1, 2. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 3. Head and Pronotum; 4. Face; 5. Genital capsule, lateral view; 6. Pygofer lateral view; 7, 8. Aedeagus lateral and dorsal view; 9, 10. Valve and subgenital plates, dorsal and lateral view; 11.Style; 12. Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2615527/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) 0.73x as wide as long and 0.76x width of scutellum; anterior margin of pronotum roundly produced between eyes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DC1236FBFFE7FF8880FB5D1E1FF6FCC2" blockId="2.[151,1436,152,1215]" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">
Male genitalia: Pygofer (
<figureCitation id="44962A7EFFE7FF8881E65D1E1C31FDAF" box="[474,594,533,556]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1850,1872]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,298,1803]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,298,1829]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Xenovarta viraktamathi sp. nov. male 1, 2. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 3. Head and Pronotum; 4. Face; 5. Genital capsule, lateral view; 6. Pygofer lateral view; 7, 8. Aedeagus lateral and dorsal view; 9, 10. Valve and subgenital plates, dorsal and lateral view; 11.Style; 12. Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2615527/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">Fig. 5 &amp; 6</figureCitation>
) longer than wide, with posterior lobe produced and terminating in dorsally directed acute processes, one on either side. Segment X stout, dorsal half sclerotized, with a caudo-ventral bifid process (
<figureCitation id="44962A7EFFE7FF8880A35D511E82FDF2" box="[159,225,602,625]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1850,1872]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,298,1803]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,298,1829]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Xenovarta viraktamathi sp. nov. male 1, 2. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 3. Head and Pronotum; 4. Face; 5. Genital capsule, lateral view; 6. Pygofer lateral view; 7, 8. Aedeagus lateral and dorsal view; 9, 10. Valve and subgenital plates, dorsal and lateral view; 11.Style; 12. Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2615527/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Valve fused to subgenital plates the latter fused to near apex with a poorly developed caudolateral process; with distal macrosetae and many fine ventral setae arranged irregularly (
<figureCitation id="44962A7EFFE7FF8883495D761A66FD17" box="[885,1029,637,660]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1850,1872]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,298,1803]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,298,1829]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Xenovarta viraktamathi sp. nov. male 1, 2. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 3. Head and Pronotum; 4. Face; 5. Genital capsule, lateral view; 6. Pygofer lateral view; 7, 8. Aedeagus lateral and dorsal view; 9, 10. Valve and subgenital plates, dorsal and lateral view; 11.Style; 12. Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2615527/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">Figs. 9 &amp; 10</figureCitation>
). Style (
<figureCitation id="44962A7EFFE7FF88845C5D761ACDFD17" box="[1120,1198,637,660]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1850,1872]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,298,1803]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,298,1829]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Xenovarta viraktamathi sp. nov. male 1, 2. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 3. Head and Pronotum; 4. Face; 5. Genital capsule, lateral view; 6. Pygofer lateral view; 7, 8. Aedeagus lateral and dorsal view; 9, 10. Valve and subgenital plates, dorsal and lateral view; 11.Style; 12. Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2615527/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) with well-developed preapical lobe, with few short spine-like setae, apophysis digitate 0.23x of the total length. Connective stem as long as arms (
<figureCitation id="44962A7EFFE7FF8880E65DC91F4AFD5A" box="[218,297,706,729]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1850,1872]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,298,1803]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,298,1829]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Xenovarta viraktamathi sp. nov. male 1, 2. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 3. Head and Pronotum; 4. Face; 5. Genital capsule, lateral view; 6. Pygofer lateral view; 7, 8. Aedeagus lateral and dorsal view; 9, 10. Valve and subgenital plates, dorsal and lateral view; 11.Style; 12. Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2615527/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
), arms closely appressed. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="44962A7EFFE7FF8882855DC91D57FD5A" box="[697,820,706,729]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1850,1872]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,298,1803]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,298,1829]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Xenovarta viraktamathi sp. nov. male 1, 2. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 3. Head and Pronotum; 4. Face; 5. Genital capsule, lateral view; 6. Pygofer lateral view; 7, 8. Aedeagus lateral and dorsal view; 9, 10. Valve and subgenital plates, dorsal and lateral view; 11.Style; 12. Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2615527/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">Figs. 7 &amp; 8</figureCitation>
), with shaft uniform in width throughout length in lateral and ventral view, abruptly tapered distally to acute apex, with pair of lateral subapical lamellate processes; gonopore large, subapical at base of lateral processes; preatrium absent; dorsal apodeme moderately well developed, tapered to narrowly rounded apex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DC1236FBFFE7FF8880FB5C461BE9FCE7" blockId="2.[151,1436,152,1215]" box="[199,1418,845,868]" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">
<emphasis id="EED9EAE9FFE7FF8880FB5C461FA1FCE7" bold="true" box="[199,450,845,868]" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">Measurements (mm) -</emphasis>
Male: 7.52 long, 1.20 wide across eyes, 0.75 length of pronotum, 1.31 width of pronotum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
