<subSubSection id="94B76570FFE7FF8880FB5CD31FE3FB92" pageId="2" pageNumber="446" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="DC1236FBFFE7FF8880FB5CD31FE3FB92" blockId="2.[151,1436,152,1215]" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">
<emphasis id="EED9EAE9FFE7FF8880FB5CD31F24FC6C" bold="true" box="[199,327,984,1007]" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named after Prof. C. A. Viraktamath in recognition of his monumental contributions to leafhopper taxonomy.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="94B76570FFE7FF8880FB5B161F2DFB3C" pageId="2" pageNumber="446" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="DC1236FBFFE7FF8880FB5B161F2DFB3C" blockId="2.[151,1436,152,1215]" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">
<emphasis id="EED9EAE9FFE7FF8880FB5B161F56FBB7" bold="true" box="[199,309,1053,1076]" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="1BAD4D78FFE7FF8881005B161C59FBB7" authority="Meshram &amp; Hashmi, 2018" authorityName="Meshram &amp; Hashmi" authorityYear="2018" box="[316,570,1052,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xenovarta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viraktamathi" status="sp.nov.">
<emphasis id="EED9EAE9FFE7FF8881005B161C59FBB7" box="[316,570,1052,1076]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">Xenovarta viraktamathi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="EED9EAE9FFE7FF88827E5B161CF2FBB7" bold="true" box="[578,657,1053,1076]" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="F5EA5792FFE7FF88827E5B161CF2FBB7" box="[578,657,1053,1076]" pageId="2" pageNumber="446" rank="species">sp.nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
runs to 
<taxonomicName id="1BAD4D78FFE7FF8882D55B161D3BFBB7" authorityName="Viraktamath" authorityYear="2004" box="[745,856,1053,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xenovarta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EED9EAE9FFE7FF8882D55B161D3BFBB7" box="[745,856,1053,1076]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">Xenovarta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Viraktamath’s (2004) key to genera, disagreeing in having a small ventral process on segment X. It also appears to differ from other species of 
<taxonomicName id="1BAD4D78FFE7FF8884AF5B4B1B61FBD4" authorityName="Viraktamath" authorityYear="2004" box="[1171,1282,1088,1111]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xenovarta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EED9EAE9FFE7FF8884AF5B4B1B61FBD4" box="[1171,1282,1088,1111]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">Xenovarta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the forewing apex rounded rather than truncate. It resembles 
<taxonomicName id="1BAD4D78FFE7FF88833B5B691A26FBFA" authority="Viraktamath" authorityName="Viraktamath" authorityYear="2004" box="[775,1093,1122,1145]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xenovarta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acuta">
<emphasis id="EED9EAE9FFE7FF88833B5B691DD9FBFA" box="[775,954,1122,1145]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="446">Xenovarta acuta</emphasis>
Viraktamath
</taxonomicName>
externally but differs from this and other species by the more rounded apex of the forewing and simple symmetrical aedeagus with a pair of subapical lateral processes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
